{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17629636","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17629636"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:08:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:08:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17291"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17291","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17291"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.61,0.1,0.06,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9981"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114436"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9981","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9981"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17291"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96437"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7229"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23377"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23380"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23520"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114436","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114436"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 25-year-old man presents with numbness and tingling on the outer aspect of his left forearm. He also cannot flex his elbow fully. His symptoms started after he dislocated his left shoulder during a game of football a week ago. He had a closed reduction of the dislocation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following nerves is most likely to have been affected?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Axillary","Musculocutaneous","Radial","Median","Ulnar"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emusculocutaneous nerve\u003C/strong\u003E is responsible for innervating the muscles that flex the elbow, such as the biceps brachii and brachialis. It also provides sensory innervation to the lateral aspect of the forearm. Injury to this nerve can result in loss of elbow flexion and sensory loss in the lateral forearm.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eaxillary nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates the deltoid and teres minor muscles, affecting shoulder abduction. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eradial nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates the posterior compartment of the arm and forearm, affecting wrist and finger extension. The \u003Cstrong\u003Emedian nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates most of the anterior forearm muscles and some hand muscles, affecting wrist flexion and thumb opposition, whilst the \u003Cstrong\u003Eulnar nerve\u003C/strong\u003E innervates some forearm and most hand muscles, affecting finger abduction and adduction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The musculocutaneous nerve is responsible for innervating the muscles that flex the elbow, such as the biceps brachii and brachialis.","The musculocutaneous nerve provides sensory innervation to the lateral aspect of the forearm.","Injury to the musculocutaneous nerve can result in loss of elbow flexion and sensory loss in the lateral forearm."],"references":["Polcaro L, Charlick M, Daly DT. Anatomy, Head and Neck: Brachial Plexus. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK531473/","Sakellariou VI, Badilas NK, Mazis GA, Stavropoulos NA, Kotoulas HK, Kyriakopoulos S, Tagkalegkas I, Sofianos IP. Brachial plexus injuries in adults: evaluation and diagnostic approach. ISRN Orthop. 2014 Feb 9;2014:726103. doi: 10.1155/2014/726103. PMID: 24967130; PMCID: PMC4045362","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96437"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17291"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96437","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96437"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-16T17:18:17+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-16T17:18:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9981"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114436"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"